craft.title: Pedro Montenegro
craft.description:
Hello,
My name is Pedro Montenegro and I was asked to write something here to briefly introduce me and the weekly show I host on Worldwide FM, No Problemo.
I was born in Rio de Janeiro and have been living in London for the final days of my hair - at least on my scalp!
For over five years I've been hosting a fortnightly show on Soho Radio called BarKino, trying to focus on the new Brazilian production and the current London scene, but not just that.
And in 2025 I started No Problemo here on Worldwide FM, completely lost and clueless, and looking forward to expanding the horizons of my furry ears.
You can also find some tributes, special shows and Brownswood Basement shows I hosted in this collection.
Hang loose!

craft.title: Worldwide Breakfast: Valentine Comar
craft.description: Every Wednesday from 8–11 AM GMT, kick off your day with Valentine Comar for a musical adventure that spans the globe! She brings fresh new music, exclusive first plays, artist interviews, live recordings, and one hour "Breakfast In…" guest mixes curated by selectors she loves. Each week offers something unique to spark your morning—whether you’re easing into the day or looking for an energy boost, let Valentine guide you through a journey around the world, exploring new sounds, rhythms, and cultures—one breakfast at a time.

craft.title: Quincy Jones Tribute
craft.description: Producer, arranger, and composer whose work encompassed virtually all forms of popular music. A titan of the music industry, Jones worked with many of the biggest names in jazz, rock, rhythm and blues, pop, and hip-hop.

craft.title: First Light: Rohan Rakhit
craft.description:
Join Rohan Rakhit – London-based DJ, actor and co-organiser of South Asian underground collective Daytimers – for a brand new weekly show on Tuesday mornings.

Each week Rohan draws on the eclecticism of the soulful and percussive sound that encapsulates his home city London. From artist, promoter and label deep dives to interviews with those pushing culture in their local music scenes.

craft.title: International Women's Day Celebration 2025
craft.description:
#IWD2025   #AccelerateAction
IWD 2025 campaign theme is 'Accelerate Action'
Collectively, we can Accelerate Action for gender equality.

Step forward in solidarity for International Women's Day (IWD) 2025 on March 8 to help #AccelerateAction. 

At the current rate of progress, it will take until 2158, which is roughly five generations from now, to reach full gender parity, according to data from the World Economic Forum.

Focusing on the need to Accelerate Action emphasizes the importance of taking swift and decisive steps to achieve gender equality. It calls for increased momentum and urgency in addressing the systemic barriers and biases that women face, both in personal and professional spheres.

So, together, let's Accelerate Action to speed up the rate of progress worldwide.

craft.title: Ghana Special
craft.description:
A celebration of the Independence Day of Ghana 2025 curated by Kwashibu Area Band and Soundway Records. 
Celebrating traditional and experimental music and from Ghana, from Highlife and Afro Rock to Jazz, Afrobeats and Afro House. Featuring Okyerema Asante, Strut Records and Klasikbeatz.

craft.title: Andrew Jervis
craft.description:
Andrew Jervis presents a monthly deep dive into new artists and tunes from the Bay Area and around the world, along with musical curios from past eras.

The show will bring together artists for interviews and includes a segment called Curators Corner, highlighting the work of human curators in the age of the algorithm. It's a summit of selection and a gathering around the love of music.
